<div id='widget_1669_1435_1283' class='content_area normal_content_area clearfix  '><h2>Who Are We?<a href="https://www.middlesexcountynj.gov/government/departments/department-of-public-safety-and-health/office-of-health-services/solid-waste-management-program/recycle-coach" target="_blank"><img src="https://www.middlesexcountynj.gov/home/showpublishedimage/837/637619550086900000" alt="Recycle Coach App" style="width: 300px; height: 209px; float: right;"></a></h2>
<p>The Division of Solid Waste Management is the agency charged with solid waste and recycling planning for Middlesex County.</p>
<p><a href="https://app.my-waste.mobi/US/NJ/Middlesex_County" target="_blank"></a></p>
<p>Our duties include:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Maintaining and updating the Solid Waste Management Plan</li>
    <li>Staff liaison to the Solid Waste Advisory Council</li>
    <li>Development of strategies to achieve our recycling and waste reduction goals</li>
    <li>Operation of residential programs including household hazardous waste and paper shred events, tire recycling program and compost bin sales.</li>
    <li>Educating residents and businesses on proper recycling and disposal methods.</li>
    <li>For more information about the Recycle Coach app, click the picture on the right</li>
</ul>
<h5>
</h5>
